<h1>About This Project</h1>

<p>
    This web application is an individual mini-project for CMPS 360. 
    It demonstrates how a C# ASP.NET Core Razor Pages application can 
    consume a custom Node.js/TypeScript API hosted on Render.com.
</p>

<h3>Architecture</h3>
<ul>
    <li>C# Web Application (ASP.NET Core Razor Pages) hosted locally or on a cloud platform.</li>
    <li>Custom API built with TypeScript and Node.js.</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL database storing course survey data.</li>
    <li>API hosted on Render.com and linked to a GitHub repository.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Technical Considerations</h3>
<ul>
    <li>The C# app uses <code>HttpClient</code> to call the API over HTTPS.</li>
    <li>JSON data is deserialized into C# model classes using <code>System.Text.Json</code>.</li>
    <li>Multiple pages (Home, All Surveys, Statistics) are all driven by the API data.</li>
</ul>
